Title: Quiet Night
---
The night is quiet and my room freshly washed.
Beside the folded quilt, I sit tending the fire.
I don’t know the lateness of the night.
The flames have burned to cold ash,
but my loving heart hasn’t cooled.
Before the cock crowed, we met and talked,
but dreams are vague.
